 <setup>
  <selectFromSequence name = "k" from = "3" to = "7" step = "1"/>
  <selectFromSequence name = "A" from = "2" to = "5" step = "1" exclude="$k"/>
  <selectFromSequence name = "c" from = "2" to = "6" step = "1" exclude="$A $k $k/2"/>
  <selectFromSequence name = "d" from = "2" to = "6" step = "1" exclude="$A $k $c"/> 
</setup>

<p>
  Consider two different differential equations
  <me>
   \frac{dy}{dt} = $k y \ \ \text{and} \ \ \frac{dy}{dt} = $k t 
  </me>
  While these two equations look algebraically similar, they have very different solutions.  In the prompts that follow, we explore why.
</p>
<p>  
  <ol marker="a.">
    <li>
      <p>
        Choose the statement that says in words what the first differential equation, <m>\frac{dy}{dt} = $k y</m>, expresses.
      </p>
      <answer><choiceInput>
        <choice><m>y</m> is a function of <m>t</m> whose derivative is <m>$k</m> times <m>t</m></choice>
        <choice><m>y</m> is a function of <m>t</m> whose derivative is <m>$k</m></choice>
        <choice credit="1"><m>y</m> is a function of <m>t</m> whose derivative is <m>$k</m> times itself</choice>
      </choiceInput>
      </answer>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Choose the statement that says in words what the second differential equation, <m>\frac{dy}{dt} = $k t</m>, expresses.
      </p>
      <answer><choiceInput>
        <choice credit="1"><m>y</m> is a function of <m>t</m> whose derivative is <m>$k</m> times <m>t</m></choice>
        <choice><m>y</m> is a function of <m>t</m> whose derivative is <m>$k</m></choice>
        <choice><m>y</m> is a function of <m>t</m> whose derivative is <m>$k</m> times itself</choice>
      </choiceInput>
      </answer>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Which of the following functions have the property that <q><m>y</m> is a function whose derivative is <m>$k</m> times <m>t</m></q>?  Check all that apply.
      </p>
      <answer selectMultiple><choiceInput>
        <choice credit="1"><m>y = <math simplify>$k/2*t^2</math></m></choice>
        <choice><m>y = $A e^{$k t}</m></choice>
        <choice><m>y = $c t^2</m></choice>
        <choice><m>y = $c e^{$k t}</m></choice>
        <choice credit="1"><m>y = <math simplify>$k/2*t^2</math> + $c</m></choice>
        <choice><m>y = <math simplify>$k/2</math> e^{$k t} + $c</m></choice>
        <choice credit="1"><m>y = <math simplify>$k/2*t^2</math> + $d</m></choice>
      </choiceInput>
      </answer>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Which of the following functions have the property that <q><m>y</m> is a function whose derivative is <m>$k</m> times <m>y</m> itself</q>?  Check all that apply.
      </p>
      <answer selectMultiple><choiceInput>
        <choice><m>y = <math simplify>$k/2*t^2</math></m></choice>
        <choice credit="1"><m>y = $A e^{$k t}</m></choice>
        <choice><m>y = $c t^2</m></choice>
        <choice credit="1"><m>y = $c e^{$k t}</m></choice>
        <choice><m>y = <math simplify>$k/2*t^2</math> + $c</m></choice>
        <choice><m>y = <math simplify>$k/2</math> e^{$k t} + $c</m></choice>
        <choice><m>y = <math simplify>$k/2*t^2</math> + $d</m></choice>
      </choiceInput>
      </answer>
    </li>    
  </ol>
</p>